cleanup_user_prompt_template:
Language hint: {language_hint}
Format: {output_format}
Speaker label replacements (apply exactly): {speaker_label_replacements}
Normalization map (apply aggressively when context matches): {normalization_hints}

Edit rules:
1) Fix spelling, punctuation, casing, grammar.
2) Fix obvious ASR/OCR mistakes and malformed terms (examples: QI->QA, Key->QA, sted->SDET when context is QA interview).
3) Remove filler, repetitions, stutters, interjections, verbal noise (e.g. 'nu', 'kak by', duplicated fragments) while preserving key meaning.
4) Keep technical terms correct and consistent (REST API, CI/CD, GitLab CI, RabbitMQ, Kafka, QA Lead, SDET, Automation QA, Vue.js, Selenium, XPath).
5) If dialogue format, keep one line per speaker: "Speaker: text".
6) Speaker labels policy: use only provided replacements; if replacement map is empty or a speaker has no mapping, keep original labels exactly (User1, User2, ...); never invent speaker names.
7) Do not invent details. If uncertain, keep original meaning conservatively.
8) Return ONLY the edited transcript text, no explanations.

Transcript chunk:
{transcript_chunk}

